{
  "stem": "1387.2",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was left alone to start walking on the other side of the track and came to a cemetery nearby, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] and I lay down and slept the night over there.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My teacher, Nachimowicz, and a young man by the name of Adam-- I don't recall his family name-- were caught the next day.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And from what I heard later on, they were thrown and ripped apart by the dogs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The dogs ripped them apart.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Of the nine, five are still alive.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] From there, I walked [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] back to my, again, to nearby my hometown in the village of Pobocz.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] When I came to a Ukrainian lady that was friendly to my parents, she just made a sign of, of a cross when she saw me.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she told me that she'll permit me to sleep in the barn overnight, but I have to disappear the next morning because her son-in-law is a policeman.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And she told me that there are Jews in the woods nearby, and I should try to contact them.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I got to go back, a little, a little bit back and tell you another incident that happened to me when we were still-- after the liquidation of the ghetto Zloczow.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "A group of us, of about 20 Jews, decided not to wait to be killed, and we decided to run away from camp, from labor camp.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] We acquired some guns, and we ran into the nearby woods.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, they were Jewish policemen.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they were people that were close to, to Warzog.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we-- and they helped us acquire some guns.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We ran away.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
